cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about image deconvolution, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel network architecture for learning deep priors, which involves optimization techniques. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on image datasets, which could also make it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
